    "long_instructions": "## Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:**  \r\nChange the condition for the last <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">while</code> loop on <strong>Line 37</strong> to <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">jesse.hasPaint()</code>, then run the program to observe the results.  \r\n\r\n**Pay attention to the print statements:**  \r\n- Before the loop starts, you'll see whether Jesse has paint.  \r\n- Inside the loop, a message prints each time the loop runs.  \r\n- After the loop, you'll see a message if the loop finishes.  \r\n\r\nWhat happens when you run the program? Do all three print messages appear? Why or why not?\r\n",
    "project_template_level_name": "CSA U1L5-Loops PBT_revised-2025",
    "reference_links": [
      "/courses/csa-2023/guides/while-loops"
    ],
    "teacher_markdown": "When changing the condition on **Line 34** from `jesse.canMove()` to `jesse.hasPaint()`, the `Painter` object no longer moves across the second row. This is because the `Painter` object runs out of paint in the first row, so the condition for this `while` loop is never `true` when this code segment is reached.",
    "name_suffix": "_oo2025",
    "ai_tutor_available": "true",
